  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Investigating idiosyncrasies in AI fiction",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.03136",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/hjuopb",
      "score": 3,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "kehn",
      "published": "2026-07-02T12:02:29Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs like GPT-4 exhibit distinct stylistic biases and repetitive tropes ('testament to', 'delve') due to RLHF alignment.",
        "Narrative structural predictability and coherence issues stem from context window limitations and next-token prediction objectives in transformer architectures.",
        "Engineers mitigate these generation artifacts using temperature scaling, Top-P tuning, and custom system instructions to bypass default safety alignments."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "What are you doing this weekend?",
      "url": "https://lobste.rs/s/rhgehk",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/rhgehk",
      "score": 13,
      "comments": 36,
      "author": "caius",
      "published": "2026-07-03T09:57:25Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Engineers use weekends for low-stakes side projects, exploring languages like Rust, Zig, or Go, and building custom compilers or database engines.",
        "Weekend tasks often focus on homelab maintenance, self-hosting services, and migrating infrastructure to declarative setups like NixOS or Docker.",
        "The Lobsters community emphasizes that resting, stepping away from screens, and doing nothing is vital to prevent developer burnout."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Arbitrary code execution breaking sandboxes in KDE Plasma",
      "url": "https://blog.kimiblock.top/2026/07/01/arbitrary-code-execution-in-kde-plasma/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ovcwkm",
      "score": 38,
      "comments": 15,
      "author": "ecksdee",
      "published": "2026-07-03T02:39:28Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Sandboxed applications like Flatpaks can bypass isolation by writing malicious files to user autostart directories or KDE configuration paths.",
        "The vulnerability leverages KDE's KConfig framework, where unsanitized shell expansions in configuration files trigger arbitrary code execution.",
        "To mitigate, restrict sandbox filesystem overrides and block write access to ~/.config, ~/.local, and sensitive D-Bus session buses."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "I Don't Maintain My Homelab",
      "url": "https://cleberg.net/blog/homelab-maintenance.html",
